Also a great series to invite someone to, an easy invite to come cabin fever January 3rd and 4th.

21:13.943 --> 21:17.907
About 17 or 18 years ago, I was walking through the Mall of America at the Nickelodeon universe.

21:18.528 --> 21:21.471
And I saw the dumbest thing I have ever seen in my life.

21:22.693 --> 21:23.554
I'm not exaggerating.

21:23.594 --> 21:24.795
I called my wife Sarah over.

21:24.935 --> 21:27.218
I went on a five minute rant.

21:27.778 --> 21:33.845
I said, are our lives so meaningless that we are now willing to pay for that?

21:34.626 --> 21:36.228
Here's a picture of what I was looking at.

21:36.248 --> 21:46.860
I was standing outside the American Girl doll store watching a grown adult braid the hair of a doll.

21:48.221 --> 21:50.864
Not a doll that they were gonna put on display in the store.

21:50.904 --> 21:55.730
Now this is a doll that some girl brought in to have her doll's hair done.

21:56.770 --> 22:01.936
If we ever find life forms on another planet, how are we gonna explain this?

22:03.278 --> 22:07.623
Like, yeah, you know, we spend money to make sure our doll's hair is done properly.

22:07.643 --> 22:10.967
That was 17 or 18 years ago.

22:11.788 --> 22:17.155
About 15 years ago, I stood in a hospital room where my wife was delivering our third child.

22:18.116 --> 22:26.066
The doctor held up the baby, still screaming attached to the umbilical cord and said, Dad, is it a boy or is it a girl?

22:27.202 --> 22:33.530
We already had two boys, so that's what I was expecting, but when those three words came out of my mouth, it's a girl.

22:34.771 --> 22:37.174
My wife and I couldn't hold back our tears of joy.

22:38.416 --> 22:44.003
We named her Isabel, and she's a testament that girls make their dads do dumb things.

22:46.866 --> 22:53.074
For instance, when Isabel was six years old, the American Girl doll of the year was named Isabel.

22:53.855 --> 22:54.896
And so what did we do?

22:55.037 --> 22:56.178
We spent a hundred bucks.

22:57.122 --> 22:58.583
on three pounds of plastic.

22:58.824 --> 23:00.285
We didn't even have a choice.

23:00.705 --> 23:04.028
I was like, but they named the three pounds of plastic is about.

23:05.350 --> 23:14.218
Then the next year for her seventh birthday, we gave her a coupon for a date with mom and dad to the American Girl Doll Store.

23:14.498 --> 23:17.621
And I said, and you can get your doll's hair done there.

23:17.661 --> 23:24.908
She ended up getting her doll's ears pierced.

23:24.928 --> 23:27.090
We spent money on that.

23:28.546 --> 23:31.449
I actually used money that I earned to have the doll's ears pierced.

23:33.212 --> 23:38.057
From there, we went to a cafe where you could eat lunch with your doll.

23:38.618 --> 23:39.439
They brought the doll out.

23:39.459 --> 23:40.060
Here's a picture.

23:40.100 --> 23:41.542
The doll sits at the high chair.

23:41.962 --> 23:44.946
They have like a saucer and some other kinds of dishes for the doll.

23:44.966 --> 23:46.087
We spent more money on that.

23:47.188 --> 23:47.769
But guess what?

23:48.930 --> 23:49.391
I loved it.

23:50.653 --> 23:52.214
I loved the American Girl doll store.

23:52.254 --> 23:55.218
I was so disappointed when it closed at the Mall of America.

23:55.554 --> 24:00.862
We would have spent Isabelle's whole eighth birthday there, birthday there, if I had somehow fallen into a quarter of a million dollars.

24:02.866 --> 24:03.827
Now, what changed?

24:05.149 --> 24:05.830
There was a birth.

24:07.253 --> 24:13.342
I had a girl and that birth changed my perspective on the American girl doll store.

24:13.362 --> 24:15.666
I've had one other experience like that in my life.

24:16.450 --> 24:19.714
If you've heard me speak before, you know that growing up, I didn't go to church as a kid.

24:19.734 --> 24:20.635
I didn't go on Christmas.

24:21.075 --> 24:21.916
I didn't go on Easter.

24:21.936 --> 24:26.642
In fact, the first time I ever walked into a church, I was wearing basketball shorts and a Wu-Tang Clan t-shirt.

24:26.702 --> 24:28.384
Wu-Tang Clan was a wrap group that I liked.

24:29.345 --> 24:30.526
But then something happened.

24:31.808 --> 24:32.749
There was a new birth.

24:34.551 --> 24:43.922
I came to believe that Jesus was a real person who walked on planet Earth and who died on a real cross to pay the penalty for your sins and for mine.

24:44.994 --> 24:50.340
And Jesus has an interesting phrase to describe that moment of belief in a person's life.

24:50.400 --> 24:52.682
He says, it's like you have been born again.

24:52.742 --> 25:05.997
In other words, all of us are born physically when we come out of our mother's womb, but Jesus says that we must be born again spiritually, that there must be a new birth in our life.

25:07.439 --> 25:09.421
And that new birth, it changes you.

25:10.802 --> 25:14.226
I went from believing that you go to heaven by being a good person.

25:14.562 --> 25:17.205
If you would have asked me at that time of my life, like, why does a person go to heaven?

25:17.486 --> 25:18.527
How does a person go to heaven?

25:18.808 --> 25:20.650
I would have said, well, you know, you just have to be a good person.

25:21.972 --> 25:25.416
And then I came to realize that it's not a good person that goes to heaven.

25:25.436 --> 25:27.279
It's someone who's been forgiven by Jesus Christ.

25:28.320 --> 25:31.124
That I was a sinner who needed a savior.

25:32.245 --> 25:35.610
I started going to church, not because I had to, but because I wanted to.

25:35.630 --> 25:38.734
I started getting rid of some things in my life.

25:38.814 --> 25:41.778
I stopped listening to music that glorified sin.

25:42.594 --> 25:44.277
I stopped using profane language.

25:44.317 --> 25:47.162
I tried to get a control of my temper and love other people.

25:48.505 --> 25:59.284
That just like my daughter's new birth changed my perspective on the American girl doll store, my new birth in Christ changed my perspective on everything.

26:00.166 --> 26:06.898
One of my friends has a son who's about 12 years old and he got in trouble about three times in one week at school.

26:07.586 --> 26:09.128
And this is a kid who normally didn't get in trouble.

26:09.188 --> 26:13.152
And so his dad sat down, he's going to have a pretty serious conversation with his son.

26:13.333 --> 26:16.056
And as he sat down, he could see his son's just lip quivering.

26:17.738 --> 26:25.767
And his son looked at his dad and he said, dad, I just need a fresh start.

26:25.787 --> 26:27.309
I wonder if any of us are feeling that way today.

26:28.751 --> 26:31.634
I wonder if there's any of us today who, God, I just need a fresh start.

26:32.514 --> 26:37.403
I just have some guilt and shame and regret from my past.

26:37.423 --> 26:39.247
God, I just need a fresh start.

26:41.070 --> 26:43.895
Or maybe there was something traumatic that happened in your life.

26:43.935 --> 26:53.874
There was a betrayal, a divorce, a breakup, and everything in you is going, God, I just need a fresh start.

26:55.170 --> 26:58.254
You can listen to self-help podcasts and read self-help books.

26:58.314 --> 27:03.941
You can try new business ventures and enter into new relationships, but that's not what our soul needs.

27:05.563 --> 27:14.454
What our soul needs is to be forgiven, to know that we can have a fresh start, to know that there can be a new birth.

27:15.636 --> 27:21.343
When God sent his son Jesus to this world, he did not send him as a ghost or a spirit.

27:21.383 --> 27:23.986
He didn't send him as a feeling in our hearts,

27:25.058 --> 27:29.205
He did not send him as a grown adult or even as an angel.

27:29.466 --> 27:35.537
He sent him as a baby, born in a little town called Bethlehem.

27:36.258 --> 27:38.823
Matthew's Gospel records what that moment was like.

27:38.843 --> 27:42.910
It says this, this is how Jesus, the Messiah or Savior was born.

27:44.252 --> 27:47.378
His mother Mary was engaged to be married to Joseph.

27:48.098 --> 27:57.270
But before the marriage took place, while she was still a virgin, she became pregnant through the power of the Holy Spirit.

27:57.290 --> 27:59.733
I don't mean to go birds and bees on you here, but this is not normal.

28:01.675 --> 28:07.823
A woman who's never had relations with a man doesn't normally become impregnated and conceive a child.

28:08.744 --> 28:16.434
Matthew goes on in the next verse, it kind of explains, he says, all this occurred to fulfill the Lord's message through his prophet.

28:17.538 --> 28:19.641
Look, the virgin will conceive a child.

28:20.001 --> 28:27.271
She will give birth to a son and they will call him a manual, which means God is with us.

28:28.773 --> 28:31.636
The prophet that Matthew is referring to is the prophet Isaiah.

28:32.458 --> 28:36.603
In the Old Testament, there's a book called Isaiah by the prophet Isaiah.

28:36.663 --> 28:40.768
And in chapter seven, verse 14, here's what the prophet Isaiah said.

28:40.788 --> 28:45.074
He said, therefore, the Lord himself will give you a sign.

28:46.050 --> 28:53.459
The virgin will conceive and give birth to a son and will call him a manual."

28:53.479 --> 28:55.642
Now, you might wonder, well, when was Isaiah written?

28:57.044 --> 28:59.527
Was Isaiah written maybe after Jesus was born?

28:59.587 --> 29:03.392
Maybe they had heard the whole story about Jesus being born to a virgin.

29:03.632 --> 29:05.635
And so then he kind of wrote that after the fact.

29:06.977 --> 29:08.178
We know that's not true.

29:09.346 --> 29:16.094
In 1949, they found some scrolls in a cave near Qumran in Syria.

29:17.316 --> 29:22.442
And in those, it's not known as the Dead Sea Scrolls, they found full copies of the book of Isaiah.

29:23.604 --> 29:27.308
And now today, through technology, they can carbon date those copies.

29:28.290 --> 29:34.297
And they found that those copies of the book of Isaiah were written hundreds of years before Jesus Christ was born.

29:35.539 --> 29:38.162
Hundreds of years before Jesus Christ was born.

29:39.618 --> 29:45.945
Isaiah said, there will be a virgin who will conceive a child by the power of the Holy Spirit.

29:47.026 --> 29:54.274
Someone once asked Larry King, who used to host a popular show on CNN, Larry King, and interviewed presidents and world leaders and celebrities.

29:54.674 --> 29:58.979
They asked him, they said, if you could interview anyone, who would it be?

30:00.100 --> 30:01.641
And what question would you ask them?

30:01.761 --> 30:04.765
Any person in history, Larry King didn't miss a beat.

30:04.785 --> 30:06.066
He said, Jesus Christ.

30:07.586 --> 30:15.357
And I would ask him if he was indeed born of a virgin, because the answer to that question would define history for me.

30:17.580 --> 30:27.533
At the center of Christmas, indeed at the center of history, is the question, was Jesus Christ born of a virgin?

30:29.216 --> 30:36.626
Did a teenage girl marry become impregnated by the power of the Holy Spirit and give birth to the Son of God?

30:37.698 --> 30:40.864
79% of Americans today say, yes, I believe that.

30:41.425 --> 30:49.059
79% of Americans believe that the virgin birth took place, which ticks off atheists and skeptics like Richard Dawkins.

30:49.981 --> 30:54.449
Richard Dawkins has called the virgin birth religious propaganda.

30:55.772 --> 31:01.202
And then he adds this, he says, it's effective with an audience of children and the unsophisticated.

31:03.074 --> 31:08.642
Bill Maher, also a critic of Christianity, joked, he said, I believed all this stuff when I was young.

31:09.523 --> 31:13.328
I believe there was a virgin birth, but then something important happened.

31:14.210 --> 31:16.112
I graduated sixth grade.

31:18.576 --> 31:19.016
Is that true?

31:21.460 --> 31:28.690
Is it true that you are childish and foolish and naive to believe that Jesus Christ was born of a virgin?

31:30.018 --> 31:34.084
William Lane Craig has his PhD from the University of Birmingham.

31:34.124 --> 31:38.370
He's considered one of the best, most famous philosophers of our day.

31:39.091 --> 31:44.459
When he was growing up as a kid, he did not believe that Jesus Christ was conceived of a virgin.

31:44.479 --> 31:46.341
He thought that was just kind of made up story.

31:47.523 --> 31:53.171
But then he got two doctorates and developed what is known as the cosmological argument for God's existence.

31:54.293 --> 31:55.154
I think that's an earful.

31:55.842 --> 32:03.094
Let me show you what the cosmological argument is for God's existence and then I'll show how this relates to what we're talking about whether Jesus was born of a virgin.

32:03.795 --> 32:08.943
Here's the cosmological argument, premise number one, everything that began to exist must have a cause.

32:10.766 --> 32:12.329
If you're kind of skeptical, think about this.

32:13.591 --> 32:16.155
Everything that began to exist must have a cause.

32:16.375 --> 32:17.557
I think most people would agree with that.

32:18.699 --> 32:22.866
You're not usually walking down the street and all of a sudden, there it was, just came out of nowhere.

32:24.098 --> 32:29.606
If something began to exist, then whatever began to exist must have had a cause.

32:30.728 --> 32:32.190
Most everybody agrees with that statement.

32:33.092 --> 32:36.777
Premise number two, our universe began to exist at some point.

32:38.179 --> 32:40.823
Now this is where for years, scientists went, no, I don't think so.

32:40.843 --> 32:42.365
Our universe has always existed.

32:42.606 --> 32:44.348
The world has always existed.

32:45.450 --> 32:53.362
But in the last several hundred years, scientists have come to believe that the universe, in fact, began to exist at a specific point.

32:54.530 --> 32:59.977
It's almost universally acknowledged by scientists today that the universe has not always existed.

33:00.918 --> 33:04.542
Here's the third point, and this is just the logical one, the universe has a cause.

33:05.704 --> 33:13.213
If everything began to exist, has a cause, and our universe began to exist, then the universe has a cause.

33:14.434 --> 33:16.637
But here's the question, what could have caused our universe?

33:18.740 --> 33:20.722
Whatever it was, it must have been

33:21.122 --> 33:25.869
a spirit or immaterial because it existed before the material world began to exist.

33:27.130 --> 33:31.497
Whatever it was, it had to have been timeless because it pre-existed time.

33:31.517 --> 33:34.681
It would have had to have been incredibly wise.

33:35.722 --> 33:38.406
The human eye is more complex than a computer.

33:38.486 --> 33:41.711
Anything that humans have ever come up with, the human eye is more complex.

33:42.973 --> 33:46.898
It would have had to have been creative when you look at the world and design that we see in the universe.

33:47.980 --> 33:49.682
It would have had to have been loving

33:51.170 --> 34:03.863
In order to create a world in which we can experience love and love other people and flourish, do you know a being that is timeless, transcendent, spirit-wise, creative, loving?

34:05.404 --> 34:07.486
That's a description of the God of the Bible.

34:09.128 --> 34:16.615
All of this brought William Lane Craig, one of the smartest philosophers of our day, to believe that there is a God who created the world.

34:17.636 --> 34:19.378
And here's what he said about the virgin birth.

34:20.322 --> 34:31.698
He said, if I really do believe in a God who created the universe, then for him to create a Y chromosome would be child's play.

34:31.718 --> 34:32.158
He's right.

34:34.141 --> 34:40.289
Jesus had to be born of a virgin because Jesus had to be fully human and fully God.

34:41.251 --> 34:49.522
He had to be fully human to represent us as humanity, but he had to be fully God, to pay the infinite penalty for our sins.

34:50.338 --> 34:57.629
Jesus had to be sinless so that he wasn't paying for his own sins, but he was paying the penalty for your sins and for mine.

34:59.252 --> 35:04.680
Jesus had to be conceived of a virgin in order to be fully human and fully God.

35:05.702 --> 35:14.876
But you might be thinking to yourself like, well, okay, I mean, I believe, put me in the 79% who believes that Jesus was born of a virgin, but why do I care?

35:16.458 --> 35:18.802
What differences that make in my life this Christmas?

35:19.778 --> 35:22.020
Here's the difference, number one, you are never alone.

35:24.443 --> 35:28.307
Isaiah said that a virgin is gonna conceive and the child will be called a manual.

35:29.428 --> 35:32.732
And I remember reading that for the first time, I'm like, well, somebody didn't get the memo because they called him Jesus.

35:34.133 --> 35:35.074
They didn't call him a manual.

35:36.356 --> 35:40.400
But then I found out what a manual means and it means God is with us.

35:41.882 --> 35:42.623
And Jesus was.

35:44.224 --> 35:49.490
When Jesus left heaven and came to earth, he did so because to be with us.

35:49.602 --> 36:00.522
to live among us, even after Jesus is death, by His Spirit, He is with us, which means that you are never alone.

36:01.504 --> 36:08.136
Years ago, they did a study of 16 women where they were given an MRI and then told that they would receive a mild shock.

36:08.156 --> 36:13.746
And while they received the shock, their brains were hooked up to some ways of measuring their stress levels.

36:14.114 --> 36:18.880
So they wanted to see like what stress levels were these women experiencing as they received this shock.

36:18.900 --> 36:24.366
But what made the experiment interesting was that these 16 women were broken up into three different groups.

36:25.267 --> 36:27.229
The first group was holding no one's hand.

36:28.371 --> 36:30.974
The second group was holding a stranger's hand.

36:32.035 --> 36:34.818
And the third group was holding their husband's hand.

36:36.761 --> 36:39.404
The group that was holding no one's hand, their stress levels were through the roof.

36:39.424 --> 36:41.266
I mean, it was just like, well, all over the place.

36:42.114 --> 36:45.822
The group that was holding a stranger's hand, they could see a little bit of a difference.

36:45.862 --> 36:47.005
It was a little bit better.

36:47.045 --> 36:54.541
The group that was holding their husband's hand had dramatically less levels of stress.

36:55.944 --> 36:57.327
The researchers concluded this.

36:57.387 --> 37:00.434
They said presence changes everything.

37:01.378 --> 37:03.943
When I first went off to college, I had just become a Christian.

37:04.103 --> 37:08.170
And one of the things that I had to make a break with my old life was to say, you know what?

37:08.190 --> 37:10.414
I'm not going to party and drink and do those things anymore.

37:10.775 --> 37:12.458
And so I made a commitment that I wasn't going to do that.

37:12.478 --> 37:15.323
But there was one night that my whole floor was going to a kegger.

37:16.445 --> 37:19.691
And my roommate at the time used to come back drunk and do kind of gross things.

37:19.731 --> 37:21.054
And I was just like, I'm not in the mood.

37:21.094 --> 37:25.522
And so I remember there was a business building across the street.

37:26.978 --> 37:29.702
And there was a bathroom down in the basement.

37:29.722 --> 37:34.971
And so I went to this basement bathroom and I sat there and I read a book.

37:34.991 --> 37:39.017
And I remember at the time thinking, this is the loneliest I have ever felt in my entire life.

37:40.620 --> 37:44.065
The next year I transferred to a school here in St. Paul.

37:44.266 --> 37:48.432
And I was praying like crazy for my roommates because it hadn't gone very well the first time.

37:48.472 --> 37:52.018
I'm like, OK, God, please bring a great roommate into my life and God answer that prayer.

37:52.642 --> 38:00.032
One of my first nights on campus, I was walking back to my townhouse, two of my roommates were walking in the other direction, and one of them said, hey, do you want to go to the prayer chapel with us?

38:01.474 --> 38:02.836
I didn't even know there was a prayer chapel.

38:03.697 --> 38:11.328
When we went to this little tiny prayer chapel, we read our Bible separately, and then we prayed together before we left, which I had never done before.

38:11.368 --> 38:14.452
I had never prayed out loud, never prayed out loud with a couple dudes.

38:15.934 --> 38:18.738
But those two dudes became two of the best friends I've ever had in my life.

38:20.034 --> 38:25.541
And from that night on, whether they came with me or not, I would go to this little prayer chapel and I would read my Bible and I would pray.

38:25.581 --> 38:29.347
And that was where Jesus became my best friend.

38:32.731 --> 38:33.813
Do you know Jesus that way?

38:35.815 --> 38:36.276
As a friend.

38:38.539 --> 38:46.770
Two years ago, my oldest son went to the same college, and so during a break in parent orientation, I grabbed my now seven-year-old daughter and I said, hey, let's wanna show you something.

38:47.778 --> 38:51.503
So we went up to this little prayer chapel and we opened the door, it looked the same, it smelled the same.

38:51.523 --> 38:55.709
And I said, this is where Jesus became daddy's best friend.

38:57.712 --> 39:12.493
And then we got down together on our knees and we prayed for her older brother that God would protect him and that he would know Jesus not just as an idea or a belief, but that he would know him as a friend.

39:15.137 --> 39:16.178
Do you know Jesus that way?

39:18.082 --> 39:19.844
Did you know him as a friend?

39:19.864 --> 39:23.329
Not just as an idea, not just as a belief, but to know him as a friend.

39:23.569 --> 39:27.054
One of my prayers for you this Christmas has been that you would not just say, you know what?

39:27.254 --> 39:28.195
I believe there's a God.

39:28.996 --> 39:31.079
I believe Jesus was born of a virgin.

39:31.099 --> 39:35.845
I mean, I go to church when I can make it, but that you would actually know Jesus as a friend.

39:36.065 --> 39:38.729
That you would be a friend of God.

39:40.211 --> 39:42.674
In the Old Testament, there's a servant, a woman named Hagar.

39:43.458 --> 39:49.527
And she belongs, she's a slave, she belongs to a couple named Abraham and Sarah, and Sarah becomes jealous of Hagar.

39:50.087 --> 39:53.692
Because Hagar's able to conceive and Sarah is not able to do that.

39:54.714 --> 39:57.117
And so she kicks Hagar out into the desert.

39:58.639 --> 39:59.320
She's all alone.

40:00.903 --> 40:02.585
She's feeling rejected and abandoned.

40:04.387 --> 40:09.074
And God comes and speaks to her in the most tender way.

40:10.594 --> 40:16.945
So much so that when Hagar talks about God after that, she refers to him this way.

40:17.005 --> 40:19.870
She says, you are the God who sees me.

40:22.595 --> 40:23.236
God sees you.

40:25.921 --> 40:26.923
He sees your tears.

40:29.027 --> 40:29.948
He sees your pain.

40:32.052 --> 40:34.476
He sees your frustration and your discouragement.

40:34.516 --> 40:35.538
He sees you.

40:37.186 --> 40:40.911
He's seen you ever since you were a little kid and he still sees you today.

40:41.011 --> 40:45.758
He is the God who sees you and you are never alone.

40:47.360 --> 40:53.409
The second difference that the birth of Christ makes in your life is this, he will give you a new heart.

40:53.429 --> 40:57.975
The Bible says that when you put your faith in Jesus Christ, you receive the Holy Spirit of God.

40:57.995 --> 41:01.240
It begins to live within you and God makes this promise.

41:01.260 --> 41:03.102
He says, I'm gonna give you a new heart.

41:04.224 --> 41:05.746
Ezekiel chapter 36.

41:07.234 --> 41:11.900
He says this, I will give you a new heart and put a new spirit in you.

41:12.260 --> 41:19.448
I will remove from you your heart of stone and give you a new heart of flesh.

41:21.571 --> 41:24.354
Maybe there's some of us today and you're going, I need a new heart.

41:26.897 --> 41:30.862
There's something in my heart, there's bitterness, there's anger, there's frustration.

41:31.182 --> 41:32.224
I have a hard heart.

41:32.484 --> 41:34.226
I've begun to drift from God.

41:36.450 --> 41:40.115
God says, when you turn to me, I will give you a new heart.

41:40.375 --> 41:44.820
I will fill that heart with life and joy and peace and hope.

41:46.522 --> 41:49.266
And all you have to do is receive it as a gift.

41:50.447 --> 41:54.292
Over the years, there's always been a Christmas gift that the whole world seems to want.

41:54.352 --> 41:59.058
I did a little research this week, and this will be kind of a trip down memory lane for some of you.

42:01.346 --> 42:06.134
But in 1983, the gift that you all wanted was the cabbage patch doll.

42:06.194 --> 42:08.077
Everybody had to have the cabbage patch doll.

42:08.097 --> 42:10.601
Then in 1985, it was pound puppies.

42:10.621 --> 42:14.487
1989, this was kind of my heyday, this was a Game Boy.

42:14.507 --> 42:16.270
I had to have the Game Boy.

42:16.290 --> 42:20.236
In 1995, it was the beanie baby.

42:20.256 --> 42:24.102
In 1996, it was the tickle me elmo doll.

42:24.423 --> 42:26.546
People were killing for that at Walmart.

42:26.626 --> 42:30.271
Then in the 2000s, we got into the iPod.

42:30.571 --> 42:33.135
Then you got into the Kindle or the Wii actually.

42:33.175 --> 42:34.657
The Kindle was next.

42:35.558 --> 42:41.747
Then, as we kind of progressed into the 2000s, Angry Birds board game was huge.

42:41.767 --> 42:44.530
Doc McStuffins doll was next up.

42:44.550 --> 42:46.994
Then you had the Elsa doll from Frozen.

42:47.034 --> 42:49.918
And then as we kind of get to the end here, you had AirPods.

42:50.639 --> 42:54.344
And the year that AirPods was number one, the Instapod was number two.

42:54.384 --> 42:55.986
So mom and dad getting in on that.

42:57.858 --> 42:59.201
Christmas is for you too, right?

42:59.221 --> 43:00.444
You got to get in on that a little bit.

43:02.889 --> 43:08.601
Every year there is a gift that the whole world wants.

43:10.285 --> 43:13.592
And every year there is a gift that God offers to the whole world.

43:15.336 --> 43:16.498
It's his son Jesus.

43:18.146 --> 43:21.033
He offers the free gift of eternal life.

43:21.053 --> 43:27.009
He offers His grace and His forgiveness and His joy and His peace and His hope and His love.

43:27.029 --> 43:29.635
He offers a new birth and a new heart.

43:31.380 --> 43:33.084
Romans chapter 6 says it this way.

43:33.104 --> 43:35.410
It says, for the wages of sin is death.

43:36.706 --> 43:38.768
A wage is something that you earn.

43:38.808 --> 43:40.871
It's something that you deserve.

43:40.911 --> 43:43.153
Some of us think, well, our sin, you know, it's not that big of a deal.

43:43.193 --> 43:43.974
Everybody makes mistakes.

43:44.034 --> 43:44.194
Sure.

43:44.495 --> 43:49.020
But he says, the wages of sin against a perfect and holy God, the penalty for that is death.

43:51.442 --> 43:55.307
Not just physical death one day, but spiritual death and separation from God.

43:57.008 --> 44:01.854
In a place that Jesus calls hell, it's separated from him from ever.

44:01.874 --> 44:05.618
He says, for the wages of sin is death, but the free gift

44:06.082 --> 44:14.210
The gift that God offers to you freely, the free gift of God is eternal life in Christ Jesus our Lord.

44:16.792 --> 44:35.570
I wanna show you the story of someone in our church who needed a new physical heart, needed a new heart into his body, but it was because of his trust in Jesus Christ that he experienced God's presence and God's comfort, going through one of the most difficult

44:36.098 --> 44:45.009
Experiences you could imagine, take a look.

44:45.029 --> 44:45.850
My name is Jennifer.

44:46.791 --> 44:51.257
I have two boys, Carver, who is 18, and Connor who is 17.

44:51.978 --> 44:54.261
My boys are my absolute blessings.

44:55.322 --> 44:58.326
I cherish every single day that I get to be their mom.

44:58.766 --> 45:04.754
And the love that we have for each other is truly remarkable.

45:05.858 --> 45:11.464
Both boys were born with congenital cell heart defects and have had multiple open heart surgeries.

45:12.004 --> 45:18.030
But we knew at birth that Connors was very serious, and we knew someday that he'd have to have a heart transplant.

45:19.692 --> 45:24.937
Even though Connors had only half a heart, his heart was bigger than anybody I know.

45:25.778 --> 45:26.298
It was full.

45:29.321 --> 45:30.082
My name's Connors.

45:30.302 --> 45:31.243
I'm 17 years old.

45:32.004 --> 45:34.066
I loved to play hockey, hang out with my friends.

45:34.978 --> 45:37.443
Growing up knowing I was sick was pretty scary.

45:37.744 --> 45:43.014
Just knowing I would eventually have to get a heart transplant was like a big thing to just have in the back of my mind.

45:43.495 --> 45:49.928
I didn't always feel sick, but like whenever I would do something active I would always have to sit down and be tired mostly.

45:50.349 --> 45:52.754
But I would always take like one day at a time.

45:55.138 --> 45:58.162
Being a mom and watching him get more sick was very hard.

45:58.342 --> 46:02.348
But Connor really rolled with every single punch of every hospital stay.

46:02.588 --> 46:06.533
Every illness or sickness that he had due to his heart not being able to keep up.

46:07.855 --> 46:11.420
Around age 16, his body was failing.

46:11.941 --> 46:12.882
So he went down to Mayo.

46:13.503 --> 46:19.311
And on December 18, 2024, they deemed him ready for a new heart.

46:20.132 --> 46:24.818
And they said, go home and enjoy the holidays and come back January 6.

46:27.106 --> 46:43.970
The first day I was in the hospital, it was really difficult knowing that I was not going to leave that building until I had a new heart, knowing it could be a week, months, years, and just sitting there not knowing when it was was probably the hardest thing.

46:45.872 --> 46:49.117
Living in the hospital, you see so much devastation and despair.

46:49.157 --> 46:55.666
You start to wonder if that's how your story is going to end up.

46:55.746 --> 46:58.931
Around day 100 became pretty tough.

47:00.272 --> 47:02.536
I was at the point where I was like, when is this going to happen?

47:03.237 --> 47:04.258
It was nerve-wracking.

47:04.779 --> 47:06.041
There was anxiety and fear.

47:06.862 --> 47:09.586
And it becomes very difficult to stay hopeful.

47:10.427 --> 47:16.816
But Connor had the strongest faith and said, Mom, this is God's plan.

47:17.036 --> 47:18.819
God will provide when it's right for him.

47:21.383 --> 47:23.826
Some ways I stayed positive was

47:24.034 --> 47:27.799
Inviting a lot of my friends to come visit, hanging out with like family.

47:28.059 --> 47:33.406
And anything that was hard in that day, we would just always ask Jesus to help us through it.

47:33.986 --> 47:35.709
I felt like Jesus was like a friend there.

47:36.129 --> 47:40.414
We could always talk to him or just pray towards him or with him.

47:42.076 --> 47:45.040
In Connor fashion, he wanted to pray every single night.

47:45.521 --> 47:48.885
And so we came up with the idea to do a prayer chain.

47:49.345 --> 47:53.010
And every single night, Connor would say the prayer and I would write it.

47:53.218 --> 47:57.543
and we added it to our protein, strung out all over the hospital room.

47:58.464 --> 48:00.767
Dear Lord, thank you for a good day.

48:01.948 --> 48:03.270
Got to go outside.

48:03.290 --> 48:07.895
I pray for everyone in the hospital, and I pray for a new heart.

48:08.636 --> 48:10.217
In your name we pray, amen.

48:10.778 --> 48:12.300
That was day 133.

48:15.303 --> 48:21.170
Fast forward, and we're on 168 days at this time inside the hospital.

48:21.442 --> 48:25.006
And on June 22nd, we're watching Eaglebrook on the TV.

48:25.466 --> 48:28.249
And Connor's favorite song of Fern Foundation is on.

48:28.630 --> 48:31.773
And my look back in Connor was crying.

48:32.334 --> 48:34.356
And I went over and I gave him a hug and a kiss.

48:35.437 --> 48:37.299
And he said, Mom, it's really close.

48:37.640 --> 48:38.420
It's coming soon.

48:38.460 --> 48:39.181
It's coming.

48:40.042 --> 48:42.104
And so I hugged him for about another minute.

48:43.166 --> 48:44.387
And the phone rang.

48:44.407 --> 48:47.190
And it was surreal.

48:48.311 --> 48:50.994
We couldn't believe that our miracle heart had come.

48:53.090 --> 48:59.938
When I heard that my doctors have accepted heart for me, the moment I was super excited because I know that this is all we've been waiting for.

48:59.998 --> 49:04.903
And I was just calling all my friends, telling them and telling my family.

49:05.363 --> 49:07.326
But it was like the night went on.

49:08.267 --> 49:11.650
And I had to go to sleep and wake up the next morning for my surgery.

49:12.091 --> 49:13.993
It was probably the hardest thing.

49:14.013 --> 49:14.934
Couldn't sleep at night.

49:14.954 --> 49:17.056
I was overwhelmed.

49:18.358 --> 49:19.439
I had my whole family around me.

49:20.600 --> 49:22.322
But it was still pretty scary.

49:31.362 --> 49:33.204
It was hard to fathom.

49:33.825 --> 49:41.294
I was gracious and thankful, but letting go of your son in the hallway before the operating room.

49:42.296 --> 49:46.081
Honestly, it was one of the most hardest things I've done in my life.

49:46.962 --> 49:52.509
But the strength that he had, I felt the presence of God during the entire moment.

49:53.370 --> 50:00.018
And I truly believed that God picked him up and held him in his hands at that point in time and took him into surgery.

50:01.538 --> 50:06.124
I almost felt like Jesus was by my side, I guess.

50:06.845 --> 50:08.687
Like, I didn't cry.

50:08.707 --> 50:15.856
I was, like, unfazed, just a straight face down the aisle, and then I got towed into surgery.

50:20.743 --> 50:29.714
So Connor went down to surgery at around 230, and that 12 hours was brutal.

50:30.562 --> 50:39.952
You get updates that the donor heart has arrived and that they are transferring the new heart into his body.

50:39.972 --> 50:44.276
And then you get updates that the new heart has been started.

50:47.239 --> 50:50.082
Connor's new heart started beating at 9.06 AM.

50:50.543 --> 50:51.924
We got to see him again at 2.30.

50:51.964 --> 50:57.330
And I got to feel his brand new heartbeat in his chest.

50:58.338 --> 51:00.981
And I broke down hard.

51:01.021 --> 51:03.223
It was everything I prayed for.

51:03.303 --> 51:12.511
God answered my prayers, answered all our prayers, and it was still so surreal that a different heart was in his body beating.

51:13.532 --> 51:14.373
But he was alive.

51:16.655 --> 51:17.276
He was alive.

51:20.099 --> 51:27.826
One big thing that Connor has always said is that getting a heart is not easy.

51:28.514 --> 51:34.064
the amount of people that have prayed for us and the support and love has carried us through.

51:34.104 --> 51:39.594
After 246 nights, Connor gets to finally go home.

51:40.275 --> 51:41.918
And it was joyous.

51:41.999 --> 51:42.580
We were happy.

51:42.720 --> 51:43.521
I mean, excited.

51:43.541 --> 51:46.066
It felt like time had stopped.

51:46.567 --> 51:50.514
And then all of a sudden, we were transported back.

51:57.250 --> 52:03.458
Last Christmas was very hard because we were preparing ourselves to go into the hospital.

52:04.399 --> 52:12.029
And so this year, Christmas Eve marks six months that Connor will have his miracle heart in him, post-transplant.

52:12.049 --> 52:22.322
And as you imagine, this is a really joyous time where we are enjoying the miracle of life inside my son.

52:22.362 --> 52:25.746
And the lights

52:27.106 --> 52:31.952
are brighter and the festivities are more fun.

52:33.974 --> 52:40.442
I know there's many angels watching over Connor this Christmas and his donor family too.

52:41.463 --> 52:44.467
It's a very special Christmas season.

52:48.472 --> 52:50.855
Knowing that the hard thing is behind me is super relieving.

52:51.656 --> 52:57.042
Just going into Christmas with a new heart, not having to worry about everything.

52:57.250 --> 52:58.472
It's super good.

52:59.334 --> 53:11.438
I just want the star to be motivating the other people and them knowing if they're going through a hard thing that they can do it with Jesus and just pray whenever you need it.

53:11.458 --> 53:14.865
If I didn't believe in Jesus, I don't know how I would have done it.

53:15.466 --> 53:17.650
I don't know how anybody can get through life without him.

53:31.970 --> 53:32.591
I agree with them.

53:34.654 --> 53:36.497
I don't know how people get through life without Jesus.

53:39.262 --> 53:42.166
Maybe today there's something in your life where you say, God, I need a new start.

53:42.427 --> 53:44.089
I need a new birth.

53:44.249 --> 53:45.892
I need a new heart.

53:47.455 --> 53:49.658
Spiritually, God, I need you to do something in my life.

53:51.361 --> 53:53.083
God is offering that to you today as a gift.

53:54.225 --> 53:55.487
It's offered to every single person.

53:56.549 --> 53:58.312
In just a moment, I'm gonna lead us in a prayer.

53:58.352 --> 53:59.794
And if you pray this prayer with me,

54:00.066 --> 54:04.873
At this booklet that you received on the way in on page three, there's just a part that says that you decide to follow Jesus today.

54:05.774 --> 54:08.238
And if you would, just take a moment after church, fill that out, drop it off.

54:08.258 --> 54:09.740
There's a little perforated part there.

54:09.780 --> 54:11.403
You can tear it off and drop it off as you go.

54:11.443 --> 54:12.945
It's also a QR code.

54:12.965 --> 54:16.009
If you want to do it after church or if you're online, there's a QR code as well.

54:16.831 --> 54:21.197
But the Bible says, if you confess with your lips and believe in your heart, that you will be saved.

54:21.958 --> 54:23.781
And so I want to lead you in a prayer to do just that.

54:23.801 --> 54:24.562
Let's pray together.

54:31.522 --> 54:35.207
Lord, there might be someone here today who says, you know what I need?

54:35.247 --> 54:35.668
That's me.

54:35.928 --> 54:36.909
I need a fresh start.

54:38.592 --> 54:40.875
My heart has begun to drift from you, God, and it's hard.

54:42.036 --> 54:43.278
It's hard towards the things of God.

54:46.002 --> 54:46.983
God, would you give me a new heart?

54:49.166 --> 54:52.450
Right now, in the quietness of their mind, they're just gonna pray, Lord, I confess my sins to you.

54:52.490 --> 54:53.271
I turn away from them.

54:55.214 --> 54:55.855
I believe God.

54:55.875 --> 55:01.042
I believe that Jesus Christ was born of a virgin.

55:02.082 --> 55:03.545
conceived by the Holy Spirit.

55:05.007 --> 55:10.316
He was the Son of God that he died on the cross to pay the penalty that I could not pay for myself, but he didn't stay there God.

55:10.597 --> 55:16.787
He rose again, defeating death and sin once and for all.

55:16.807 --> 55:27.666
God, right now in this moment, I receive as a gift, salvation through Jesus Christ, the promise and the hope of eternal life, your grace and your mercy.

55:30.210 --> 55:33.515
God, there are others of us here who might be going through a difficult time in our life.

55:34.356 --> 55:36.860
God, we just need your comfort and your peace.

55:38.001 --> 55:41.046
We need to know that you're close, God, and to sense your presence in our life.

55:42.207 --> 55:45.292
I pray this Christmas, God, that we would, that we would sense your presence and your love.

55:46.694 --> 55:48.076
And God, we are so thankful.

55:49.598 --> 55:57.810
We are so thankful for this Christmas that you did not stay in heaven, but you left heaven and you came to earth to live among us so that we could know you, God.

55:58.594 --> 56:02.285
Not just as a believer and idea, but to know you as a friend and so, Lord, thank you.

56:03.388 --> 56:04.952
Thank you for what a friend we have in Jesus.

56:06.336 --> 56:07.219
Pray it all in his name.

56:08.222 --> 56:08.542
Amen.

56:09.505 --> 56:10.428
Merry Christmas, everybody.

56:10.769 --> 56:12.594
We'll see you the weekend after January.

